[2026-03-04T05:02:23Z] [unknown] n++{"conversation_id":"2a12bd8d-f3eb-4225-a92c-586e34e15094","generation_id":"fa0ef714-7f2c-4528-983f-8ce9ef5386b3","model":"claude-4.6-sonnet-medium-thinking","tool_name":"Read","tool_input":{"file_path":"G:\\trent_rules\\.trent\\tasks\\task013_memory-rest-endpoint.md"},"tool_output":"{\"file_path\":\"G:\\\\trent_rules\\\\.trent\\\\tasks\\\\task013_memory-rest-endpoint.md\",\"content_length\":3598}","duration":158.132,"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01E34Rcdk6ftb6hyiE66b78w","hook_event_name":"postToolUse","cursor_version":"2.5.26","workspace_roots":["/g:/trent_rules"],"user_email":"fstrent@gmail.com","transcript_path":"c:\\Users\\FSTrent\\.cursor\\projects\\g-trent-rules\\agent-transcripts\\2a12bd8d-f3eb-4225-a92c-586e34e15094\\2a12bd8d-f3eb-4225-a92c-586e34e15094.jsonl"}

[2026-03-04T05:02:23Z] [unknown] n++{"conversation_id":"2a12bd8d-f3eb-4225-a92c-586e34e15094","generation_id":"fa0ef714-7f2c-4528-983f-8ce9ef5386b3","model":"claude-4.6-sonnet-medium-thinking","tool_name":"Write","tool_input":{"file_path":"G:\\trent_rules\\.trent\\tasks\\task013_memory-rest-endpoint.md","content":"---\nid: 13\ntitle: 'Implement Memory REST Endpoint + pgvector Storage'\nstatus: completed\npriority: high\nphase: 0\nsubsystems: [mcp-server, database, memory]\nproject_context: 'Completes the server-side storage for the memory capture system. Hooks and adapters already POST to /memory/ingest but the endpoint does not exist.'\ndependencies: [1, 2]\nstatus_changed: '2026-03-03T23:36:40Z'\nestimated_effort: '3-5 days'\nstory_points: 5\n---\n\n# Task: Implement Memory REST Endpoint + pgvector Storage\n\n## Objective\nCreate the `/memory/ingest` REST endpoint in the trent MCP server (`docker/trent/`) that receives session data from the Claude and Cursor adapters and stores it in PostgreSQL with pgvector embeddings for semantic search.\n\n## Background\nThe memory capture system has a complete client-side pipeline:\n- **Hooks**: `.claude/hooks/agent-complete.ps1` and `.cursor/hooks/agent-complete.ps1` fire on session end\n- **Adapters**: `claude_adapter.py` parses JSONL sessions, `cursor_adapter.py` parses SQLite `state.vscdb`\n- **Both POST to**: `http://localhost:8082/memory/ingest`\n\nThe POST payload structure (already defined by adapters):\n```json\n{\n  \"project_id\": \"string (from .trent/.project_id)\",\n  \"conversation_id\": \"string (session UUID)\",\n  \"platform\": \"claude_code | cursor_ide | gemini_antigravity | vscode_claude\",\n  \"status\": \"completed | partial\",\n  \"user_id\": \"string (from ~/.trent/user_config.json)\",\n  \"machine_id\": \"string (deterministic per machine)\",\n  \"turns\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user | assistant\",\n      \"content\": \"string\",\n      \"tool_names\": [\"list of tools used\"],\n      \"files_referenced\": [\"list of file paths\"],\n      \"timestamp\": \"ISO 8601\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `POST /memory/ingest` endpoint exists in trent MCP server\n- [ ] Validates incoming payload structure (project_id, conversation_id, platform required)\n- [ ] Creates `memory_sessions` table in PostgreSQL:\n  - `id` (UUID primary key)\n  - `project_id` (text, indexed)\n  - `conversation_id` (text, unique)\n  - `platform` (text)\n  - `status` (text)\n  - `user_id` (text)\n  - `machine_id` (text)\n  - `turn_count` (int)\n  - `summary` (text, nullable - populated later by Tier-2)\n  - `embedding` (vector(1536), nullable - for semantic search)\n  - `created_at` (timestamptz)\n  - `updated_at` (timestamptz)\n- [ ] Creates `memory_turns` table:\n  - `id` (UUID primary key)\n  - `session_id` (FK to memory_sessions)\n  - `turn_index` (int)\n  - `role` (text)\n  - `content` (text)\n  - `tool_names` (text[])\n  - `files_referenced` (text[])\n  - `embedding` (vector(1536), nullable)\n  - `timestamp` (timestamptz)\n- [ ] Generates embeddings for turn content using existing pgvector infrastructure\n- [ ] Returns `{\"ingested_turns\": N, \"session_id\": \"uuid\"}` on success\n- [ ] Returns appropriate error codes (400 bad payload, 500 server error)\n- [ ] Idempotent: re-posting same conversation_id updates rather than duplicates\n- [ ] Database migrations created (or auto-create on startup)\n\n## Implementation Notes\n- The trent MCP server already uses FastMCP and PostgreSQL\n- Reuse the existing pgvector embedding infrastructure from the RAG system\n- The endpoint runs on port 8082 (same as trent MCP server)\n- Consider batching embedding generation for large sessions (50+ turns)\n- Adapters already handle retry logic client-side\n\n## Files to Create/Modify\n- `docker/trent/mcp/plugins/memory.py` (new - main plugin)\n- `docker/trent/mcp/models/memory.py` (new - Pydantic models)\n- `docker/trent/mcp/db/memory_schema.sql` (new - table definitions)\n- `docker/trent/mcp/server.py` (modify - register memory plugin)\n"},"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01E34Rcdk6ftb6hyiE66b78w","hook_event_name":"preToolUse","cursor_version":"2.5.26","workspace_roots":["/g:/trent_rules"],"user_email":"fstrent@gmail.com","transcript_path":"c:\\Users\\FSTrent\\.cursor\\projects\\g-trent-rules\\agent-transcripts\\2a12bd8d-f3eb-4225-a92c-586e34e15094\\2a12bd8d-f3eb-4225-a92c-586e34e15094.jsonl"}

