[2026-03-04T05:02:30Z] [unknown] n++{"conversation_id":"2a12bd8d-f3eb-4225-a92c-586e34e15094","generation_id":"fa0ef714-7f2c-4528-983f-8ce9ef5386b3","model":"claude-4.6-sonnet-medium-thinking","tool_name":"Write","tool_input":{"file_path":"G:\\trent_rules\\.trent\\tasks\\task014_memory-mcp-tools.md","content":"---\nid: 14\ntitle: 'Implement MCP Memory Tools (5 tools)'\nstatus: completed\npriority: high\nphase: 0\nsubsystems: [mcp-server, memory]\nproject_context: 'Creates the MCP tools that AI agents call to capture summaries, search memory, and load context. These are the Tier-2 (active) and Tier-3 (query) interfaces.'\ndependencies: [13]\nstatus_changed: '2026-03-03T23:36:40Z'\nestimated_effort: '2-3 days'\nstory_points: 5\n---\n\n# Task: Implement MCP Memory Tools (5 tools)\n\n## Objective\nImplement the 5 MCP tools referenced in rules and CLAUDE.md that allow AI agents to actively capture and query session memory.\n\n## Tools to Implement\n\n### 1. `memory_ingest_session` (Tier 1 - passive)\n**Purpose**: Called by file adapters (claude_adapter.py, cursor_adapter.py) to ingest raw turns.\n**Parameters**:\n- `project_id` (str, required)\n- `conversation_id` (str, required)\n- `platform` (str, required): claude_code | cursor_ide | gemini_antigravity | vscode_claude\n- `turns` (list, required): Array of turn objects\n- `status` (str, optional): completed | partial\n**Returns**: `{\"ingested\": true, \"turn_count\": N, \"session_id\": \"uuid\"}`\n**Notes**: This is essentially the MCP wrapper around the REST `/memory/ingest` endpoint from Task 013.\n\n### 2. `memory_capture_session` (Tier 2 - active self-report)\n**Purpose**: AI agent calls this before ending a session to self-report a summary.\n**Parameters**:\n- `project_id` (str, required)\n- `conversation_id` (str, optional - auto-generated if not provided)\n- `platform` (str, required)\n- `summary` (str, required): 2-3 paragraph session summary\n- `key_decisions` (list[str], optional): Important decisions made\n- `files_changed` (list[str], optional): Files modified during session\n- `status` (str, optional): completed | partial | in-progress\n**Returns**: `{\"captured\": true, \"session_id\": \"uuid\"}`\n**Notes**: Stores summary + generates embedding. This is what `20_agent_memory_gemini.md` and `20_agent_memory_vscode.md` rules tell agents to call.\n\n### 3. `memory_search` (Tier 3 - semantic query)\n**Purpose**: Semantic search over captured session memory.\n**Parameters**:\n- `query` (str, required): Natural language search query\n- `project_id` (str, optional): Filter to specific project\n- `platform` (str, optional): Filter by platform\n- `limit` (int, optional, default=5): Max results\n- `days_back` (int, optional): Only search within N days\n**Returns**: Array of matching sessions with relevance scores, summaries, and metadata.\n\n### 4. `memory_sessions` (Tier 3 - list/browse)\n**Purpose**: List recent sessions for a project.\n**Parameters**:\n- `project_id` (str, required)\n- `limit` (int, optional, default=10)\n- `platform` (str, optional): Filter by platform\n**Returns**: Array of session summaries sorted by recency.\n\n### 5. `memory_context` (Tier 3 - context injection)\n**Purpose**: Returns a token-budgeted context block for session-start injection.\n**Parameters**:\n- `project_id` (str, required)\n- `max_tokens` (int, optional, default=2000): Budget for context block\n- `focus` (str, optional): Topic to prioritize in context selection\n**Returns**: Formatted markdown context block with most relevant recent session summaries.\n**Notes**: This is what `session-start.ps1` should eventually call to inject prior session memory.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] All 5 tools registered in trent MCP server tool list\n- [ ] `memory_ingest_session` stores raw turns (wraps Task 013 endpoint)\n- [ ] `memory_capture_session` stores AI-generated summaries with embeddings\n- [ ] `memory_search` returns semantically relevant sessions\n- [ ] `memory_sessions` lists recent sessions with metadata\n- [ ] `memory_context` returns token-budgeted context markdown\n- [ ] All tools visible in MCP tool discovery (`.claude/settings.local.json`)\n- [ ] Error handling: graceful failures with descriptive messages\n- [ ] Tools documented in CLAUDE.md MCP tools table\n\n## Implementation Notes\n- Build as a FastMCP plugin in `docker/trent/mcp/plugins/memory.py` (extend Task 013 file)\n- Reuse pgvector similarity search from existing RAG implementation\n- `memory_context` should use cosine similarity to find most relevant sessions, then truncate to token budget\n- Consider caching for `memory_context` (called every session start)\n\n## Files to Create/Modify\n- `docker/trent/mcp/plugins/memory.py` (extend from Task 013)\n- `docker/trent/mcp/server.py` (register new tools)\n- `CLAUDE.md` (update MCP tools table)\n- `agents.md` (update MCP tools table)\n"},"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_0172gpQoZ46weDuqnZgjvcyT","hook_event_name":"preToolUse","cursor_version":"2.5.26","workspace_roots":["/g:/trent_rules"],"user_email":"fstrent@gmail.com","transcript_path":"c:\\Users\\FSTrent\\.cursor\\projects\\g-trent-rules\\agent-transcripts\\2a12bd8d-f3eb-4225-a92c-586e34e15094\\2a12bd8d-f3eb-4225-a92c-586e34e15094.jsonl"}

