[2026-03-04T05:02:37Z] [unknown] n++{"conversation_id":"2a12bd8d-f3eb-4225-a92c-586e34e15094","generation_id":"fa0ef714-7f2c-4528-983f-8ce9ef5386b3","model":"claude-4.6-sonnet-medium-thinking","tool_name":"Read","tool_input":{"file_path":"G:\\trent_rules\\.trent\\tasks\\task015_memory-adapter-fallback.md"},"tool_output":"{\"file_path\":\"G:\\\\trent_rules\\\\.trent\\\\tasks\\\\task015_memory-adapter-fallback.md\",\"content_length\":3291}","duration":2.269,"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01M7GuSwy22JoTD93wjH4XxZ","hook_event_name":"postToolUse","cursor_version":"2.5.26","workspace_roots":["/g:/trent_rules"],"user_email":"fstrent@gmail.com","transcript_path":"c:\\Users\\FSTrent\\.cursor\\projects\\g-trent-rules\\agent-transcripts\\2a12bd8d-f3eb-4225-a92c-586e34e15094\\2a12bd8d-f3eb-4225-a92c-586e34e15094.jsonl"}

[2026-03-04T05:02:37Z] [unknown] n++{"conversation_id":"2a12bd8d-f3eb-4225-a92c-586e34e15094","generation_id":"fa0ef714-7f2c-4528-983f-8ce9ef5386b3","model":"claude-4.6-sonnet-medium-thinking","tool_name":"Write","tool_input":{"file_path":"G:\\trent_rules\\.trent\\tasks\\task015_memory-adapter-fallback.md","content":"---\nid: 15\ntitle: 'Add Fallback Mechanism to Memory Adapters'\nstatus: completed\npriority: medium\nphase: 0\nsubsystems: [hooks, memory]\nproject_context: 'Makes the existing adapters resilient when the MCP server is offline. Currently they silently fail in background jobs.'\ndependencies: []\nstatus_changed: '2026-03-03T23:36:40Z'\nestimated_effort: '1 day'\nstory_points: 2\n---\n\n# Task: Add Fallback Mechanism to Memory Adapters\n\n## Objective\nUpdate `claude_adapter.py` and `cursor_adapter.py` to gracefully handle MCP server unavailability by writing session data to a local fallback file that can be ingested later.\n\n## Background\nCurrently when the adapters POST to `http://localhost:8082/memory/ingest` and the server is down:\n- The HTTP request fails silently in a background PowerShell job\n- Error is logged to `.claude/logs/` or `.cursor/logs/` but no data is preserved\n- Session data is lost permanently\n\n## Changes Required\n\n### claude_adapter.py (~line 850, POST section)\n```python\ntry:\n    response = urllib.request.urlopen(req, timeout=10)\n    # success path\nexcept (urllib.error.URLError, urllib.error.HTTPError, TimeoutError) as e:\n    # FALLBACK: Write to local file\n    fallback_path = os.path.join(project_root, '.trent', 'memory_fallback.md')\n    write_fallback(fallback_path, session_data, error=str(e))\n```\n\n### cursor_adapter.py (~same pattern)\nSame try/except/fallback pattern.\n\n### Fallback File Format\n```markdown\n## Session: {conversation_id}\n**Platform**: {platform}\n**Timestamp**: {ISO 8601}\n**Status**: fallback (server unavailable)\n**Error**: {error message}\n**Turns**: {turn_count}\n\n### Summary\n{auto-generated brief summary from turns}\n\n### Files Referenced\n{list of files from turns}\n\n---\n```\n\n### Session-Start Ingestion\nUpdate `session-start.ps1` to check for `.trent/memory_fallback.md`:\n- If file exists and has content, attempt to POST each session block to `/memory/ingest`\n- On success, remove the ingested block from the file\n- On failure, leave for next session\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] claude_adapter.py catches POST failures and writes to `.trent/memory_fallback.md`\n- [ ] cursor_adapter.py catches POST failures and writes to `.trent/memory_fallback.md`\n- [ ] Fallback file uses append mode (multiple failed sessions accumulate)\n- [ ] Fallback entries include enough data to reconstruct the session\n- [ ] session-start.ps1 attempts to drain fallback file on next session\n- [ ] Fallback file is in `.gitignore` (contains session data)\n- [ ] Adapters log clearly whether they used primary or fallback path\n\n## Implementation Notes\n- This task has NO dependencies - can be done before Tasks 013/014\n- The fallback makes the existing adapters useful even without the server\n- Keep fallback format simple - markdown is human-readable for debugging\n- Don't try to embed in fallback - just store raw data for later processing\n\n## Files to Modify\n- `.cursor/hooks/claude_adapter.py` (add try/except + fallback write)\n- `.cursor/hooks/cursor_adapter.py` (add try/except + fallback write)\n- `.claude/hooks/claude_adapter.py` (mirror changes)\n- `.claude/hooks/cursor_adapter.py` (mirror changes)\n- `.cursor/hooks/session-start.ps1` (add fallback drain)\n- `.claude/hooks/session-start.ps1` (add fallback drain)\n- `.gitignore` (add `.trent/memory_fallback.md`)\n"},"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01M7GuSwy22JoTD93wjH4XxZ","hook_event_name":"preToolUse","cursor_version":"2.5.26","workspace_roots":["/g:/trent_rules"],"user_email":"fstrent@gmail.com","transcript_path":"c:\\Users\\FSTrent\\.cursor\\projects\\g-trent-rules\\agent-transcripts\\2a12bd8d-f3eb-4225-a92c-5