[2026-03-04T05:02:43Z] [unknown] n++{"conversation_id":"2a12bd8d-f3eb-4225-a92c-586e34e15094","generation_id":"fa0ef714-7f2c-4528-983f-8ce9ef5386b3","model":"claude-4.6-sonnet-medium-thinking","tool_name":"Read","tool_input":{"file_path":"G:\\trent_rules\\.trent\\tasks\\task016_memory-e2e-testing.md"},"tool_output":"{\"file_path\":\"G:\\\\trent_rules\\\\.trent\\\\tasks\\\\task016_memory-e2e-testing.md\",\"content_length\":3429}","duration":5.779,"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_0154hM5XbWKF8UgLboutA3Lk","hook_event_name":"postToolUse","cursor_version":"2.5.26","workspace_roots":["/g:/trent_rules"],"user_email":"fstrent@gmail.com","transcript_path":"c:\\Users\\FSTrent\\.cursor\\projects\\g-trent-rules\\agent-transcripts\\2a12bd8d-f3eb-4225-a92c-586e34e15094\\2a12bd8d-f3eb-4225-a92c-586e34e15094.jsonl"}

[2026-03-04T05:02:44Z] [unknown] n++{"conversation_id":"2a12bd8d-f3eb-4225-a92c-586e34e15094","generation_id":"fa0ef714-7f2c-4528-983f-8ce9ef5386b3","model":"claude-4.6-sonnet-medium-thinking","tool_name":"Write","tool_input":{"file_path":"G:\\trent_rules\\.trent\\tasks\\task016_memory-e2e-testing.md","content":"---\nid: 16\ntitle: 'End-to-End Memory System Testing'\nstatus: completed\npriority: medium\nphase: 0\nsubsystems: [hooks, mcp-server, memory, database]\nproject_context: 'Validates the complete memory capture pipeline from hook trigger through storage to retrieval.'\ndependencies: [13, 14, 15]\nstatus_changed: '2026-03-03T23:36:40Z'\nestimated_effort: '1 day'\nstory_points: 2\n---\n\n# Task: End-to-End Memory System Testing\n\n## Objective\nCreate and execute a comprehensive test plan that validates every link in the memory capture chain.\n\n## Test Plan\n\n### Test 1: Adapter GåÆ REST Endpoint (Tier 1)\n**Setup**: Start trent MCP server with memory plugin\n**Steps**:\n1. Manually trigger `claude_adapter.py` with `--session-id test-001`\n2. Verify POST to `/memory/ingest` succeeds\n3. Query database: `SELECT * FROM memory_sessions WHERE conversation_id = 'test-001'`\n4. Verify turns stored in `memory_turns` table\n5. Verify embeddings generated\n\n**Expected**: Session + turns stored, embeddings populated\n\n### Test 2: MCP Tool - memory_capture_session (Tier 2)\n**Steps**:\n1. Call `memory_capture_session` via MCP with test summary\n2. Verify session stored with summary text\n3. Verify embedding generated from summary\n4. Call `memory_search` with query related to summary\n5. Verify test session appears in results\n\n**Expected**: Summary stored, searchable via semantic query\n\n### Test 3: MCP Tool - memory_search (Tier 3)\n**Steps**:\n1. Ingest 5 test sessions with distinct topics\n2. Search for each topic by natural language\n3. Verify correct session ranked first each time\n4. Test `days_back` filter\n5. Test `project_id` filter\n\n**Expected**: Semantic search returns relevant results with correct ranking\n\n### Test 4: MCP Tool - memory_context (Tier 3)\n**Steps**:\n1. Ingest 10 test sessions\n2. Call `memory_context` with `max_tokens=2000`\n3. Verify output is valid markdown\n4. Verify token count is within budget\n5. Verify most recent/relevant sessions included\n\n**Expected**: Token-budgeted context block with relevant sessions\n\n### Test 5: Fallback Mechanism\n**Steps**:\n1. Stop trent MCP server\n2. Trigger `claude_adapter.py`\n3. Verify `.trent/memory_fallback.md` created with session data\n4. Restart trent MCP server\n5. Trigger `session-start.ps1`\n6. Verify fallback file drained (content ingested, file emptied)\n\n**Expected**: Data preserved during outage, ingested on recovery\n\n### Test 6: Full Pipeline (Hook GåÆ Adapter GåÆ Server GåÆ Query)\n**Steps**:\n1. Start a Claude Code session in a test project\n2. Perform some work (create a file, read a file)\n3. End the session (triggers hook)\n4. Wait 30 seconds for background job\n5. Call `memory_sessions` for the project\n6. Verify session appears with correct metadata\n7. Call `memory_search` with query about the work done\n8. Verify session found semantically\n\n**Expected**: Complete pipeline works automatically\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] All 6 test scenarios pass\n- [ ] No silent failures in any pipeline step\n- [ ] Error messages are descriptive when things fail\n- [ ] Performance acceptable: ingest < 5 seconds for 50-turn session\n- [ ] Search returns results in < 1 second\n- [ ] Test scripts created in `temp_scripts/` for repeatable testing\n\n## Files to Create\n- `temp_scripts/test_memory_ingest.py` (Tests 1-2)\n- `temp_scripts/test_memory_search.py` (Tests 3-4)\n- `temp_scripts/test_memory_fallback.py` (Test 5)\n- `temp_scripts/test_memory_e2e.ps1` (Test 6 - PowerShell for hook testing)\n"},"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_0154hM5XbWKF8UgLboutA3Lk","hook_event_name":"preToolUse","cursor_version":"2.5.26","workspace_roots":["/g:/trent_rules"],"user_email":"fstrent@gmail.com","transcript_path":"c:\\Users\\FSTrent\\.cursor\\projects\\g-trent-rules\\agent-transcripts\\2a12bd8d-f3eb-4225-a92c-586e34e15094\\2a12bd8d-f3eb-4225-a92c-586e34e15094.jsonl"}

